Definition: optical device consisting of a transparent cell with two electrodes between two polarizing media
Example: passes light only if the two planes of polarization are parallel; used as a high-speed shutter or to modulate a laser beam
Synonyms: optical_device, optical, device, consisting, of, a, transparent, cell, with, two, electrodes, between, polarizing, media, passes, light, only, if, the, planes, polarization, are, parallel, used, as, high-speed, shutter, or, to, modulate, laser, beam
Category: noun.artifact
